{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11854", "repo": "rails", "body": "@dmathieu but only true, false is an acceptable value as well. it seems that the right way to handle booleans is as any other preset-acceptable-value field, with the inclusion validator. but in that case the error produced is not the right one. for a missing value you'll get \"xxx must be one of true, false\" and not \"xxx can't be blank\". the presence validator must support booleans as well in my opinion.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d0a9bd3543c151007d07"}, "issue_id": 11854, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/22507819", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11854#issuecomment-22507819", "updated_at": "2013-08-12T16:54:58Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar", "login": "eladmeidar", "gravatar_id": "dfdf85290b9351c578d718c98c352bb1", "html_url": "https://github.com/eladmeidar", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/dfdf85290b9351c578d718c98c352bb1?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F85bbbcff1e1ac5dae544e0a76eedde4b.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 29753, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eladmeidar/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-08-12T16:54:58Z", "id": 22507819, "owner": "rails"}
